,Recommended,393430,28509238,"Posted: 21 December, 2016",all,Bob Lee Swagger,"Love this simulator!Being from Northern Minnesota I'm a huge ice fisherman and when I don't have time to get out this is a fun way to get my fix. Multiple lakes, ponds and rivers to try and fish along with a plethra of different fish species (half I've never even heard of but that's becauese they're European fish species). So far it's a pretty simple game. I like to compare fishing to golf, a day to learn and a lifetime to master. I think I've had more luck just using a baitless balanced lure over the baited types as long as you are jigging like a madman the fish seem to come flyin up the hole (assuming you found a good spot). Graphics leave a bit more to be desired and I have no idea what the point of the jump feature is but it's there. I've never had much urge to try any VR but this game makes me want to.Some funny points:-The animation is a bit on the basic side but for $15 what can you expect.-I would pay to watch someone take off at a full sprint wearing a snowsuit, carrying a hand auger/drill, all their fishing gear, a chair and whatever fish they've caught (sometimes 20+) running all around a lake like Usain Bolt. If you've ever ice fished you know that equipment isn't exactly light. Your character must be a well conditioned, finely tuned athlete to sprint a mile, hand auger 10-20 holes and carry all that equipment. Just cracks me up.-The wildlife running around on the lake is a funny addition. I've read there's apparently a bear somewhere in this game as well.Cons:-Online mode. When I looked for online action the 3 servers offered were all empty. However, if you have a few friends that own this you can set up a tournament for all of you to play in.-Music. This game could really use more than the one 15 second loop that will drive you insane if listened to too long. Also reminds me ALOT of Golf with my Friends music.Being a pureblood Minnesotan I've been ice fishing ever since I was a wee lad. Here I am at 29 years old still doing it whenever I get a chance. However, there are many days I just don't have time to make it out on the lakes so when this was brought to my attention I was immediately interested. I was hesitant to buy this but the large majority of the reviews seemed positive and it happened to go on sale for $10 while watching it so I decided to pull the trigger. This game has yet to disappoint and already provided me more entertainment than I anticipated. So I highly suggest this to anyone who enjoys some simple ice fishing or has never tried it even.Side note: My brother came up with what I thought would be a funny idea for my Live-stream and to get a VR setup outside in the Northern MN elements... Sit outside in the real cold winter weather while fishing for fake fish. Really want to do that once haha."
