,Recommended,393430,28276924,"Posted: 9 December, 2016",all,Garce,"The interface IS a bit unintuitive at first. Initially, I was ""THIS CLOSE"" to asking for a refund, but - wanting a relaxing game experience - I stuck with it. Note: Long tournaments and short competitions are NOT actually relaxing. But free-fishing is digital zen.I haven't ice-fished (in real life) for decades, but it was something I loved doing when I was a kid. Sigh, nostalgia... So, I gave this game another shot. After maybe an hour of play, I began to figure things out. The equipment you purchase (with in-game cash earned by catching fish, by winning competitions and tournaments) makes a HUGE difference to your success. This is not instant gratification - its a slow burn.I am 40 hours into the game now, and I haven't yet explored a third of what it offers. While I might not always win - I always feel that my failures are my fault, and not because of the RNG. This is a game that I feel I can play for years. Go back to that old map... try this bait... catch that slightly bigger fish... break my record...I will admit that it is hard to get a grasp on the controls in the beginning - it is not very intuitive out of the gate. But Ice Lakes IS worth taking your time with.AND... I just caught a 32 lb sturgeon so WOOHOO! YAY ME!10/10 Will buy games made in Finland again."
